cs.CC, cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.NT, cs.GT. 

The paper deals with the computational complexity of graph properties and their eventual evasiveness under number theoretic hypotheses. This connects the fields of computer science and number theory, making cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.NT (Number Theory) the most likely categories. The paper also involves the analysis of permutation groups and their connection to prime numbers, which falls under cs.GT (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper deals with graph theory and its properties, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) a possible category as well.
